# s2 = 'We propose the Chambent(Champion-Challengers) algorithm for making an \emph{online} choice of hyperparameters in online learning settings.  The approach relies upon an oracle that can propose plausible perturbations of a configuration and is guaranteed to eventually lead to an optimal setting so long as one of the proposed perturbations yields superior performance.  Given this application-dependent oracle, Chambent handles the process of determining a champion and scheduling a set of live challengers based on sample complexity bounds.  Empirically, we show that Chambent provides good performance across a wide array of datasets when optimizing over representation/featurization decisions.'


# levenshtein(s1, s2)